\test_input{
\: Big integer string conversion with non-decimal bases.
\: Covers cowel_big_int_to_string case 2 (binary), case 8 (octal),
\: case 16 (hexadecimal), and the default case (arbitrary base).
\: Also covers the uppercase-letter path in cowel_big_int_from_string.

\cowel_to_str( 0x100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000, base=2)
\cowel_to_str( 0x100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000, base=3)
\cowel_to_str( 0x100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000, base=8)
\cowel_to_str( 0x100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000, base=16)
\: 0xFFFF...FFFF (32 uppercase F's) triggers uppercase-letter parsing in big integer from-string
\cowel_to_str(0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF)
}

